# Voya — Teaser Campaign Plan (Soft Launch, Late June → August 2026)

## Context

Voya is Malaysia's verified travel marketplace (brand hierarchy **Trust → Float & Match → Smart Search**), targeting a full product launch by **end of 2026**. Before then, the founder wants to **build a social presence on TikTok + Instagram from now (20 June) through August** that puts the *name* "Voya" in front of Malaysian travellers **without revealing what the business actually does** — a mystery/anticipation play that grows a warm, relevant audience so the eventual reveal lands on a crowd that's already waiting.

This plan defines: the **teaser strategy**, the **optimum posting cadence** (per day / per week), the **volume of assets required** (video / carousel / stills), and a **content-pillar + phasing framework**. It deliberately stops short of writing all ~60 individual posts — once this framework is approved, we plan the day-by-day content and then generate everything through **Higgsfield** (with the founder's go-ahead).

**Locked decisions (from founder):**
- **Angle:** Travel-themed mystery — wanderlust-adjacent visuals that attract the *right* audience (Malaysian travellers) but never explain the marketplace mechanic.
- **Capacity:** Solo founder + Higgsfield AI → cadence must be lean and sustainable for one person.
- **Language:** Bilingual — English-led with Bahasa Malaysia woven in (KL/Selangor traveller voice).

**Brand guardrails (from `Voya/Branding/voya_strategy_c.md`):** Indigo (#3C1DDE primary) + Gold (#EAA520 accent); DM Serif Display (taglines, italic), DM Sans (body/eyebrows), DM Mono (labels); the four-pointed-star wordmark logo (`Voya/Business/Voya.png`) is the only authorised mark — never recolour/stretch/rotate. During the teaser we lead with the **star motif and the name**, NOT the Trust/Float/Search features (those are held back for the reveal).

