## Strategy: the three-phase teaser arc

The teaser runs ~10 weeks and escalates intrigue without ever explaining the product. The reveal of *what Voya is* begins after August; full launch is end of year.

| Phase | Weeks (approx.) | Goal | Energy |
|---|---|---|---|
| **A — "Whisper"** | Late Jun, wks 1–3 | Plant the name + star mark; pure aesthetic intrigue. Establish the visual world. | Quiet, beautiful, zero explanation |
| **B — "Curiosity"** | July, wks 4–7 | Grow followers + waitlist; make people *ask* what Voya is. Engagement bait. | Playful, interactive, "coming soon" undertone |
| **C — "Anticipation"** | August, wks 8–10 | Ramp the countdown; signal "something for Malaysian travellers is coming"; drive waitlist signups. Set up the Sept reveal. | Urgent, building, FOMO |

**Hard rule for the whole teaser:** show the name, the star, and the *feeling* of travel — never the Trust badge, Float & Match flow, or Smart Search. The category (travel) may be *hinted* through visuals from Phase A and stated more openly only in Phase C.

