## Optimum cadence (solo-sustainable)

**Hero platform = TikTok** (cheapest place for a mystery teaser to go viral). Instagram runs in parallel, fed largely by repurposed TikToks (watermark removed) + native Stories.

### Per day
- **1 hero short-form video** (8–15s), posted to **both** TikTok and IG Reels. 6 days/week (1 rest day).
- **Instagram Stories: daily**, 3–5 lightweight frames (polls, countdown stickers, reposts, BTS, "guess what Voya is").

### Per week
| Asset | Qty/week | Platform |
|---|---|---|
| Hero short-form videos (8–15s) | **6** | TikTok + IG Reels (same asset) |
| Carousel (6–8 slides) | **1** | IG feed + TikTok photo-mode |
| Story sets (3–5 frames) | **7** | IG Stories (TikTok Stories optional) |

### Volume over the full ~10-week teaser
- **~60 hero videos** (6/wk × 10)
- **~10 carousels** (1/wk)
- **~70 story sets** (daily)
- Net unique production is lower because every TikTok = the IG Reel.

**Best posting times (MYT):** TikTok ~12–1pm and 7–10pm; IG Reels ~12pm and 8–9pm; Stories spread morning + evening. Validate against in-app analytics after week 2 and adjust.

**Hashtag/handle hygiene:** secure and post under `@voya` handles + `#Voya`; mix small branded tags with broad Malaysian travel tags (#cutimalaysia #travelmalaysia #jalanjalan) so Wanderlust posts get discovered by the target audience.

